Jeff writes:

>RSA is a poison, too damn many people think it's god's gift.  Anything
>involving RSA is 100% safe.  It's not.

I agree.

>There is no need to use RSA here, it does not help in any way over the
>original encryption scheme.  As Andy pointed out, if the client does
>the encryption, joe twink just has to grab the packets and steal the
>encrypted string directly from the packet.  Echoing this encrypted
>scheme then verifies that I am indeed MUCUS PIG.

Well, this can be remedied.  The packet can include both the password
and some random text the server sends the client.  Then no two encryptions
would be the same.  crypt (3) is one-way, but RSA can decrypt things,
that's the difference.

T.
